defs.docs: Implements `SmallString`, a `String`-like container for small strings

defs.name: SmallString
defs.docs: A `String`-like container that can store a small number of bytes inline.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Construct an empty string.

defs.name: with_capacity
defs.docs:
Construct an empty string with enough capacity pre-allocated to store
 at least `n` bytes.

defs.name: from_str
defs.docs: Construct a `SmallString` by copying data from a `&str`.

defs.name: from_string
defs.docs: Construct a `SmallString` by using an existing allocation.

defs.name: from_buf
defs.docs: Constructs a new `SmallString` on the stack using UTF-8 bytes.

defs.name: from_buf_unchecked
defs.docs:
Constructs a new `SmallString` on the stack using the provided byte array
 without checking that the array contains valid UTF-8.

defs.name: inline_size
defs.docs: The maximum number of bytes this string can hold inline.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the length of this string, in bytes.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns `true` if this string is empty.

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs: Returns the number of bytes this string can hold without reallocating.

defs.name: spilled
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the data has spilled into a separate heap-allocated buffer.

defs.name: drain
defs.docs: Empties the string and returns an iterator over its former contents.

defs.name: push
defs.docs: Appends the given `char` to the end of this string.

defs.name: push_str
defs.docs: Appends the given string slice to the end of this string.

defs.name: pop
defs.docs: Removes the last character from this string and returns it.

defs.name: grow
defs.docs: Reallocates to set the new capacity to `new_cap`.

defs.name: reserve
defs.docs:
Ensures that this string's capacity is at least `additional` bytes larger
 than its length.

defs.name: reserve_exact
defs.docs:
Ensures that this string's capacity is `additional` bytes larger than
 its length.

defs.name: shrink_to_fit
defs.docs: Shrink the capacity of the string as much as possible.

defs.name: truncate
defs.docs: Shorten the string, keeping the first `len` bytes.

defs.name: as_str
defs.docs: Extracts a string slice containing the entire string.

defs.name: as_mut_str
defs.docs: Extracts a string slice containing the entire string.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Removes all contents of the string.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Removes a `char` from this string at a byte position and returns it.

defs.name: insert
defs.value: fn (&mut self, idx: usize, ch: char) -> ()
defs.docs: Inserts a `char` into this string at the given byte position.

defs.name: insert_str
defs.docs: Inserts a `&str` into this string at the given byte position.

defs.name: as_mut_vec
defs.docs: Returns a mutable reference to the contents of the `SmallString`.

defs.name: into_string
defs.docs:
Converts the `SmallString` into a `String`, without reallocating if the
 `SmallString` has already spilled onto the heap.

defs.name: retain
defs.docs: Retains only the characters specified by the predicate.

defs.name: Drain
defs.docs: A draining iterator for `SmallString`.

defs.name: FromUtf8Error
defs.docs: A possible error value when creating a `SmallString` from a byte array.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: Returns the slice of `[u8]` bytes that were attempted to convert to a `SmallString`.

defs.name: into_buf
defs.docs: Returns the byte array that was attempted to convert into a `SmallString`.

defs.name: utf8_error
defs.docs: Returns the `Utf8Error` to get more details about the conversion failure.
